docs.text: of the major horror sub-genres , vampire movies are easily the most adaptable .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: think about it .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: frankenstein movies haven't changed all that much because they still need that mad-scientist-in-bavarian-castle setting .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: if you made a frankenstein movie today , you'd have to have the monster be a virus or something -- and outside of michael j . fox , there aren't any actors that could play a virus convincingly .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: movies about mummies would still have to be set in egypt .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: there's not much you can do with werewolves except take them to london or paris , unless you want to have a teenage werewolf or something .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: ( and there's that michael j . fox thing again . )
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but you can have vampires do anything , and you can place them in any genre you want , just about .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: you can have traditional vampire movies ( bram stoker's dracula ) or have the anne rice version ( interview with the vampire ) , or play it for laughs ( vampire in brooklyn ) .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: you can put vampires in locales from sunny southern california ( the lost boys ) to squalid mexican dives ( from dusk till dawn ) to your local high school ( buffy , the vampire slayer ) .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: were it not redundant , you could have a movie about a law firm full of vampires .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: any day now , i expect we'll see a movie about a vampire third baseman who has to decide whether to play a day game in order to break the home run record .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: or , you can insert the vampire legend into a hong kong action movie -- and when you do that , you get blade .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: wesley snipes has the chow yun fat role in this movie -- the silent , expressionless hit man who destroys everything in his path .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: in this case , the everything happens to be vampires that explode into cgi shards instead of dead , bleeding corpses .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: snipes has less to say here than as the fugitive in u . s . marshals , but does a demonstrably better job here as a half-vampire wreaking vengeance on the bloodsuckers .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: blade is a silent , brooding presence , laying waste to vampires without a shred of remorse .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: he is as cold as his silver-bladed sword , as single minded as his garlic-filled bullets .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: yet , he's not without quirks : blade drives a battered muscle car and has to glean rolex watches from his vampire victims in order to stay solvent .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: like any good hong kong movie , blade is heavy on the chopsocky action .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: for some reason , blade spends a lot more time using his kung fu artistry than using the traditional anti-vampire weapons of garlic and silver .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: ( blade dismisses a man-portable arc lamp as being too heavy , although it looks to be a more efficient tool to dispatch vampires . )
docs.label: positive

docs.text: unfortunately , the guiding hand of john woo is absent from this film , relegating blade to the status of the replacement killers , which it most strongly resembles .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the replacement killers is the last movie i saw that i didn't review -- mostly because it made no impression on me , and i couldn't remember anything other than noise , violence , and the intensity of fat's performance .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: blade has a little more going for it , and has the vampire myth to draw from -- but other than that , it's the same kind of movie -- exciting , with well choreographed action scenes , but with no resonance .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: with a stronger villain ( stephen dorff is ( pardon the pun ) curiously bloodless as the head vampire , leaving us to wonder what denis leary might have done with the role ) , a wittier script , and a strong supporting cast , blade might have been able to rise beyond the level of commonplace summer entertainment .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: as it is , blade is an average action movie that serves to do nothing but remind us that the summer movies just keep getting dumber and the vampire movies just keep multiplying .
docs.label: positive
